displayName":"Robert Muir","active":true},"created":"2011-12-07T02:00:29.340+0000","updated":"2011-12-07T02:00:29.340+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12534126/comment/13164068","id":"13164068","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rcmuir","name":"rcmuir","emailAddress":"rcmuir at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=rcmuir&avatarId=10150","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=rcmuir&avatarId=10150","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=rcmuir&avatarId=10150","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=rcmuir&avatarId=10150"},"displayName":"Robert Muir","active":true},"body":"also on a general note, i don't like how we don't test this addIndexes(FIR) stuff very well, and i don't like the FieldOption api \r\nthat it uses for this, its really just a duplicate of the FieldInfos api in my opinion.\r\n\r\nlong term I think we should:\r\n# somehow test this better by doing addIndexes(SlowMultiReaderWrapper(segment), ...) behind the scenes in RandomIndexWriter?\r\n# maybe in 4.0 try to clean up FieldInfos and have IR return it, nuking this FieldOption API so that we dont have \"two different ways we merge\" ?","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rcmuir","name":"rcmuir","emailAddress":"rcmuir at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=rcmuir&avatarId=10150","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=rcmuir&avatarId=10150","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=rcmuir&avatarId=10150","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=rcmuir&avatarId=10150"},"displayName":"Robert Muir","active":true},"created":"2011-12-07T02:06:45.473+0000","updated":"2011-12-07T02:06:45.473+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12534126/comment/13164101","id":"13164101","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rcmuir","name":"rcmuir","emailAddress":"rcmuir at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=rcmuir&avatarId=10150","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=rcmuir&avatarId=10150","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=rcmuir&avatarId=10150","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=rcmuir&avatarId=10150"},"displayName":"Robert Muir","active":true},"body":"here's a hack patch (don't think its committable) fixing the bug.\r\n\r\ni also modified TestTypePromotion to sometimes do addIndexes with SlowMR, and its passing.\r\n\r\nBut i'm still left confused as to how or if fieldinfos is correct in this type-promotion case (who sets it to the new merged type?)\r\n","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rcmuir","name":"rcmuir","emailAddress":"rcmuir at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=rcmuir&avatarId=10150","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=rcmuir&avatarId=10150","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=rcmuir&avatarId=10150","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=rcmuir&avatarId=10150"},"displayName":"Robert Muir","active":true},"created":"2011-12-07T03:06:12.898+0000","updated":"2011-12-07T03:06:12.898+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12534126/comment/13164105","id":"13164105","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=cmale","name":"cmale","emailAddress":"gento0nz at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Chris Male","active":true},"body":"{quote}\r\nmaybe in 4.0 try to clean up FieldInfos and have IR return it, nuking this FieldOption API so that we dont have \"two different ways we merge\" ?\r\n{quote}\r\n\r\nI feel in the long term this is the best way to go.  FieldOption just feels like another way to describe field properties and we already have a few of those.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=cmale","name":"cmale","emailAddress":"gento0nz at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Chris Male","active":true},"created":"2011-12-07T03:11:06.590+0000","updated":"2011-12-07T03:11:06.590+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12534126/comment/13164117","id":"13164117","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=rcmuir","name":"rcmuir","emailAddress":"rcmuir at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=rcmuir&avatarId=10150","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=rcmuir&avatarId=10150","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=rcmuir&avatarId=10150","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=rcmuir&avatarId=10150"},"displayName":"Robert Muir","active":true},"body":"pa